FBIS3-45481 "drchi012_p_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 Central-South Region Vice Minister To Inspect Grain Prices in Hunan HK1401152494 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 10 Jan 94 HK1401152494 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [Text] Bai Meiqing, vice minister of the Ministry of Internal Trade and concurrently director of the State Grain Reserve Administration, came to Changsha City on 9 January to inspect how the city controlled grain and oil prices. Accompanied by Vice Governor Zhou Shichang as well as provincial and Changsha City grain bureau leaders, Vice Minister Bai Meiqing went to grain shops in Wuyi Zhonglu, Renminlu, and Taipingjie, where he carefully checked the price tags as well as the grain and oil quality and asked about grain and oil sales. To implement instructions of the State Council, 400.5 million kg of grain has been dumped onto the markets throughout the province to control grain prices. Grain departments have been active in transporting grain and in ensuring variety, quality, quantity, prices, and service. Since the period before the New Year, all grain departments have openly sold their grain with price tags, thus speedily reducing grain and oil prices throughout the province.
